Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you don’t have symptoms.

The Republic of Congo authorities have introduced a number of measures in response to the coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic.
On 21 March the authorities announced the closure of places of worship, schools, higher education institutions, bars and nightclubs; the prohibition of gatherings of more than 50 people as well as of family events such as weddings and funerals; and the closure of all borders except for cargo ships and flights.
On 28 March the authorities announced further measures, including prohibiting people from leaving home, except for workers providing essential goods and services, and essential travel; the closure of all shops except those selling food and essential products; establishment of a curfew from 20:00 – 05:00; and the mobilisation of defence and security forces to ensure compliance with the new measures.
These measures will be in place for a 30-day period from Tuesday 31 March 2020.
